The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Oct. 23. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
POLLUTE-DIESEL _ A new report, released just as the Phoenix area
enters the winter pollution season, traces the Brown Cloud directly
to the exhaust pipes of the very same motorists who lament the
stain it leaves on the Valley's horizon. It documents that diesel
engines spew out a disproportionate share of the microscopic bits
of soot and grime that create the visible pollution. And it
discounts the belief that the desert terrain is the reason why the
Phoenix metro area is bedeviled by a Brown Cloud. By MARY JO PITZL.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WILSON-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ It was just the kind of tasty morsel a
critic of TV news loves to munch. A new nightly newscast, featuring
anchors and reporters wearing bikinis and Speedos, is coming soon
on cable TV, reported Brill's Content. What a sterling example of
how shallow TV news is becoming, I thought. Checking into the
story, however, I found that Brill's report on the half-naked
newscast was half-baked, the kind of slipshod journalism the
watchdog magazine routinely skewers. By STEVE WILSON. Column will
move in the ``K'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
