announce a plan to reduce government spending across the board by
1.4 percent. The cuts, a total of $4.5 billion below the amounts
Congress has approved for federal departments and agencies in the
current fiscal year, would apply in the current fiscal year to
every government program for which Congress controls the annual
financing but not to benefit programs like Social Security and
Medicare. By David E. Rosenbaum.
