</P>
<P>
   This has disappointed many of the protesters who helped to drive
Suharto from the presidency last year and who saw Miss Megawati as
the preeminent people's choice.
</P>
<P>
   Their sense of having been cheated may perhaps be muted by the
selection of Miss Megawati as Wahid's vice-president. Yet it would
be quite wrong to see Wahid either as a supporter of the old regime
or as an enemy of democracy.
</P>
<P>
   Conservative he certainly is, but his opposition to Suharto is
