NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SUNDAY, OCTOBER 24
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Sunday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A picture caption last Sunday about the Olympic runner Evelyn
Ashford, with a front-page article about the long friendship
between her coach, Pat Connolly, and another former Olympian,
Willye White, misstated the year in which Ashford was shown
competing in Seoul. It was 1988, not 1984.
</P>
<P>
   Because of an editing error, an automobile review of the
Mitsubishi Eclipse last Sunday misstated the car's production site.
As noted in a graphic with the review, it is Normal, Ill., not
Japan.
</P>
