<HEADER>
A6292 &Cx1f; tad-z
u r BC-CAR-NASCAR-ADVANCE24-     10-23 0469
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAR-NASCAR-ADVANCE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mayfield in running for top 10 Cup finish
 &HT;    By Michael Carvell
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ROCKINGHAM, N.C. _ Forgive Jeremy Mayfield for sounding a bit
overconfident on his chances in today's Pop Secret 400.
</P>
<P>
   Mayfield has been overwhelmed with frustration, disappointment
and bad luck on the track this season, especially during the past
two months. Earning a front-row starting position has a tendency to
return a struggling driver's brashness. Mayfield starts in the No.
2 spot.
</P>
<P>
   ``We really want to win the race, and we feel like we can,''
Mayfield said. ``This team right now is better than it has ever
been, and I feel real good about that.''
</P>
<P>
   Mayfield, who drives the No. 12 Ford, is in such a confident
mood that he has the same outlook for the three remaining races at
Phoenix, Miami and Atlanta Motor Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wouldn't be surprised if we ran really well at all four
tracks, and I wouldn't be surprised if we won all four races,''
Mayfield said. ``That's not a prediction. That's just the way
everybody on this team feels about the last four races of the
season and about those four race tracks.''
</P>
<P>
   Mayfield, 30, was projected as one of the top contenders for the
Winston Cup championship at the beginning of the season. The lofty
expectations transpired after Mayfield's eye-opening performance
during 1998. He won the first Pocono race and had 12 top 5s, 16 top
10's and finished seventh in the points race.
</P>
<P>
   Mayfield has not won this season, but he has four top 5s and 10
top 10s. He is 11th on the points list.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're determined to fight our way back to the top,'' Mayfield
said. ``We've been trying to find what we need in our cars, from a
balance standpoint. We got off a little bit at the beginning of the
year and feel like now we know what we need.
</P>
<P>
   ``Last year, I think we all hit it and got lucky and ran good
several times and didn't know why. Now we've figured out what it
takes to run good week-in and week-out. You've gotta have answers
to build a consistent team.''
</P>
<P>
   The best way for Mayfield to salvage the season would be to win
a race and finish in the top 10 in points. He trails Mike Skinner,
in the 10th spot, by 225 points and is four points ahead of Terry
Labonte.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have to keep in mind that everything we're doing right now
affects more than just the end of this season,'' Mayfield said.
``How we end this season will play in big part in how we start next
year, and how we start next year will really affect how we finish
next year.''
</P>
<P>
   Mayfield's recent streak of bad luck included a flat tire at
Dover Downs, losing two laps because of a caution flag at
Martinsville, and ignition problems at Talladega.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
