<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-NFL-ARENA-SIDE-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ARENA LEAGUE MORE THAN JUST A FEEDER FOR NFL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD OBERT  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Just because quarterback Kurt Warner and wide receiver Oronde
Gadsden are making names for themselves in the NFL, don't think the
Arena Football League will become a feeder system.
</P>
<P>
   The rules of the two games are as different as checkers and
chess, but, in essence, it's the same: They still have to tackle
and run and pass and catch and score.
</P>
<P>
   And the quality of players in the Arena game, although 70
percent of them had experience at an NFL camp, keeps improving.
</P>
<P>
   Iowa Barnstormers owner Jim Foster, who invented the eight-man,
50-yard Arena game, said he has heard talk that the NFL soon will
assign someone to oversee relations with the Arena league and with
the Canadian Football League.
</P>
<P>
   That could open more doors for guys considered on the bubble of
being NFL players, guys such as Rattlers offensive specialist
Calvin Schexnayder.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you're good enough to play for (Rattlers Coach) Danny
White, then most of them are good enough for us to take a look at
it,'' Cardinals General Manager Bob Ferguson said. ``Any game of
football is a training ground. We tell the players, `Go get
experience.' ''
</P>
<P>
   NFL Europe still is the NFL's main training ground. That's where
Warner went for seasoning after three years in the Arena league
with the Barnstormers.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's even grown into a pretty competitive scenario,''
Ferguson said.
</P>
<P>
   Sherdrick Bonner, the former Rattlers quarterback who was signed
by the Cardinals last week, said that he had noticed the
competition grow in the smaller professional leagues just in his
seven years in the Arena league.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are thousands of other guys just trying to get into the
Arena league and the CFL,'' Bonner said.
</P>
<P>
   Last winter, the NFL started a partnership with the Arena league
and purchased an option to buy an interest sometime down the road.
Some NFL owners have expressed interest in buying Arena teams. The
New Orleans Saints ownership already has purchased a team that is
expected to begin play next Arena season.
</P>
<P>
   Rattlers President Bryan Colangelo said the kind of interest the
Arena league is getting from the NFL ``speaks volumes'' for what it
has accomplished since the league's inception in 1987.
</P>
<P>
   But it's not a farm league.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're not just doing the Arena deal to build a farm
league,'' Foster said. ``They're really more interested in the
marketing aspect, reaching more fans.
</P>
<P>
   ``This Arena Football League may not be a bad league after all.
You can't look at it as a fluke.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
