<P>
   &QL; 
BACTERIA _ What started five years ago as just a little drip in the
computer center of a major corporation has grown to a flood of
nationwide concern that fire-sprinkler systems are at risk of being
ruined by bacteria found in drinking water. The pinhole-size leak
discovered in May 1994 was one of many that began turning up in
overhead sprinkler pipes at the hub for worldwide computer
operations of AlliedSignal Inc. in Tempe, Ariz. The problems caused
by industrious bacteria hadn't been given much attention in
fire-safety systems until AlliedSignal pursued the issue _ and an
estimated $25 million in replacement costs _ in federal court
lawsuits blaming Phoenix and Tempe, its water providers. By JON
KAMMAN. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NEW-ECONOMY _ In an age when their parents were playing with
blocks, first-graders at a west Phoenix elementary school are
snapping shots of spheres and cubes with a digital camera and
printing them from the classroom computer. These are the faces of
the New Economy. It's a jittery, fast-paced world where the way we
do things is changing dramatically _ and constantly. To help
Arizona prosper in this daunting new landscape, the Morrison
Institute for Public Policy will release a New Economy guide for
Arizona. By DAWN GILBERTSON. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) In the morning she drove to Buckeye to
visit with one of the dying. Now it was afternoon and she was on
her way to visit another one of the dying. This was the life of
Eloise Delgado. It's what she did. She was never late. She never
missed an appointment, not until this particular Tuesday afternoon,
Oct. 19, when Eloise herself was one of the dying but did not know
it. By EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories. &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Undated) _ They're the words no one in television wants
to hear: ``Rework the pilot.'' But they're the ones the producers
of Time of Your Life, the Jennifer Love Hewitt spinoff of Party of
Five, heard. The series premiere begs the question: If this is the
new, improved version, how bad must the original have been? By BILL
GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
