<HEADLINE>
KIDD MAY SIT TILL SEASON OPENER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By AL TOBY  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Ja &UR; son Kidd and the Philadelphia 76ers'  &UR; Allen Iverson
might be put on hold until the regular season.
</P>
<P>
   Kidd sat out Saturday's practice because of a deep bruise on his
left thigh. Kidd suffered the injury in a collision with Los
Angeles Lakers forward  &UR; A.C. Green in Friday's preseason victory.
He is listed as day-to-day.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns (3-2) will host their third preseason game at the
America West Arena tonight at 6 against the 76ers (2-2). If Kidd
has to sit out tonight's game, he will only have to wait until
November 4th's regular-season home opener to get another crack at
Iverson.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns' injury list, however, isn't as bad as the 76ers'.
Philadelphia limps into tonight's preseason contest with a battered
frontcourt.
</P>
<P>
   Forward  &UR; Theo Ratliffe is sidelined for the next three weeks
with a fractured bone in his left ankle. Ratliffe suffered the
injury in a collision with New York Knicks guard  &UR; Charlie Ward in
the team's second preseason game.
</P>
<P>
   Fellow frontcourt men,  &UR; Matt Geiger, Tyrone Hill and  &UR; Stanley
Roberts, a recent acquisition, are also hampered by various
injuries.
</P>
<P>
   A weakened Sixers frontcourt should give the Suns a chance to
exercise their inside game on offense. Forward  &UR; Rodney Rogers was
impressive off the bench in the Suns' 112-100 preseason victory
against the Lakers. Rogers, a free-agent acquisition, scored 32
points and grabbed seven rebounds. &QL; 
Oh, behave &QL; 
Didn't the Bad Boys era end in the early 1990s?
</P>
<P>
   Obviously not, judging by the behavior of the Phoenix Suns
during the exhibition season.
</P>
<P>
   A day after  &UR; Penny Hardaway did his best imitation of  &UR; Mike
Tyson against Miami guard  &UR; Rex
 &UR; Walters, Suns forward  &UR; Tom Gugliotta was ejected after he was
called for his second technical foul of the game. Gugliotta tossed
a towel at referee  &UR; Tim Donaghy while Coach  &UR; Danny Ainge argued
with Donaghy at midcourt.
</P>
<P>
   Ainge and Gugliotta said they didn't expect a suspension as a
result of the incident.
</P>
<P>
   ``Googs is certainly not going to be suspended,'' Ainge said.
``I don't know what he did to constitute a suspension. I'm not even
sure he deserved to be kicked out of the game.''
</P>
<P>
   In a much less recalcitrant mood, Gugliotta said he should have
shown more restraint during the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I should have just kept my mouth shut,'' Gugliotta said. ``The
whole thing was stupid. You'e just got to live and learn.'' &QL; 
Kudos &QL; 
Ainge praised his team's overall defensive intensity in Friday's
victory against the Lakers. Although the Lakers shot over 50
percent and  &UR; Shaquille O'Neal had 37 points, the Lakers' second
leading scorer,  &UR; Ron Harper, had only 14 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
