of preparing and serving a formal dinner. Mrs. Starkey's
10-year-old school, based in a Georgian mansion near the Colorado
Capitol dome, now graduates about 60 certified household managers a
year. She plans to expand next year with a second training mansion
in the Washington area. (Kevin Moloney/New York Times Photo)
</P>
